The Duke, 54, vehemently denies the allegations against him. Maxwell, the daughter of disgraced tycoon Robert Maxwell, has also denied the claims. 

It is believed that the house, bought by Maxwell in 1997, is now being rented out. 

Neighbours told the Sunday Mirror they were unaware of anything untoward occurring there, but one said she had seen Andrew and two of his protection officers in the street several years ago.  

'I’ve no idea where he was going. They were walking quickly,' she said.  

A spokesman for Maxwell did not comment on the house.

Roberts, a US citizen, waived her anonymity in an interview with The Mail On Sunday in 2011, in which she claimed she had been sexually exploited by Epstein - a former friend of the Duke.

